The massive wildfire still raging in the California wilderness may have been sparked by a illegal marijuana farm.

During a press conference Friday, Todd McNeal, chief of Northern California's Twain Harte Fire Department, said that they now know that the fire was 'human caused' as there wasn't any lightening in the area when the fire started August 17.

While they don't know what for sure started the fire, McNeal said that they 'highly suspect that it might have been some sort of illicit grove, marijuana-grow type of thing.'

