At one point the fire grew to the size of Chicago, and smoke from the flames have spread thousands of miles away to Canada and the Great Lakes with traces of the smoke showing up in Europe as well.

The fire has destroyed an estimated 213,414 acres which makes it the fifth larges wildfire in California history. 

It has destroyed hundreds of buildings as well as threatened giant sequoias and San Francisco's power and drinking water.

